                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d793">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Gresham</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Riddle</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1894-04-20">
                            <hi rend="italic">April 20, 1894</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Aivazian’s passport duly issued, naturalized April 20, 1890, Fresno, California,
                    and left United States immediately, declaring purpose to return in ten or twelve
                    months. Circumstances protracting his stay in Turkey and acts done there should
                    be investigated. Press for opportunity to do so.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
